FT  14 OCT 92 / Award to honour FT photographer
AN ANNUAL photographic award has been established in memory of Alan Harper,
the Financial Times photographer killed last year in an accident in a
Kuwaiti oilfield.
The Alan Harper Bursary will provide photographers and photographic
technicians with a grant of up to Pounds 5,000 to fund an assignment.
Applicants must be under the age of 26 on January 1 1993 and be a full-time
employee in photography or a photographic student.
Full details are available from The Alan Harper Bursary, Financial Times, 1
Southwark Bridge, London SE1 9HL. The scheme, made possible by a grant from
British Telecom, is in association with the British Journal of Photography.
